name: Spice Goa

reviews.review_text: In a quest to search for the best Goan fish thali, we landed here on a weekend during lunch hours and oh boy, it was a painful wait of an hour in the scorching heat. Even after we had booked a table for 8 the previous night through Easy Diner platform, the restaurant denied and did not honour our booking because of an issue between them and the Easy Diner platform. We were seated on the top deck after an hour and we ordered a few Fish Thalis, King Fish masala fry, egg fried rice, chicken lollipops, Goan veg platter and veg biryani and a few drinks to go with it. As soon as the thali arrived, we started belting and collectively decided that this was the best Goan Fish thali out of all the thalis we had during our 6-day trip to Goa. The prawns curry, the boneless fish fry, the sides to go with it were all very tasty and fulfilling. Even the barfi on the plate was too good. Chicken lollipops and egg fried rice were great too. King Fish masala fry was a bit sour to our taste and was not liked by everyone. The server did give us a heads up about it before we ordered it, so it's all good. The only disappointment was the Goan veg platter. Paying a premium for such less veg sides was not a good plan and the items did not taste very well either. Overall, it was a great experience devouring Goan fish thali and other seafood and chicken items here. A worthy visit and I highly recommend this place for other tourists/travellers. The restrooms were neat and clean and the sinks were kept well and tidy too. The restaurant has won a lot of awards and accolades and the same has been stuck on the wall and one can witness it while going to the top deck. The only nitpicking here i would do is the cramped space and how tiny the restaurant and the waiting area is. It is a very cramped space and a 6 feet human has to bend and watch their head on the top deck while walking around. Even the crowd gets too busy and takes away the ambience of having good food. The waiting area is overfilled during peak lunch hours and one has to stay back in the heat while their family and/or friends wait in the car with the comfort of air conditioning until they get a table confirmation.

Great food, Service and atmosphere is good too.
You can try goan food and north Indian as well.

Overhyped restaurant. The cramped & noisy ambience is a telltale of the obnoxious & rude service being provided by the outlet. We found no tissues on the table,no water was offered,no finger bowls & a general apathy towards customers. The food at best was decent. Nothing to match the hype. Plenty of brilliant restaurants in Goa. Makes no sense visiting this restaurant. Not recommended.

description:
### Discovering Spice Goa: A Culinary Jewel in Mapusa

If you‚Äôre on the hunt for a culinary gem in Goa, **Spice Goa** might just be your next destination. With a solid rating of **4.4 out of 5** from **5,300 reviewers**, this restaurant is drawing attention for its authentic Goan cuisine, particularly its **fish thali**‚Äîa dish that has become a hallmark of customer praise. Central to many reviews are keywords like ‚Äú**Goan**‚Äù (mentioned 361 times), ‚Äú**thali**‚Äù (209 mentions), ‚Äú**serradura**‚Äù (68 mentions), and ‚Äú**banana leaf**‚Äù (55 mentions). Spice Goa is not only a place to eat; it's an experience to savor.

### Ambiance & Design

Stepping into Spice Goa, you may find the atmosphere to be bustling since the restaurant tends to be crowded, especially during peak hours. The d√©cor is designed with local charm in mind, featuring elements that resonate with Goan culture, albeit some reviewers have found it cramped. The top deck, accessible through a cozy staircase adorned with accolades on the walls, presents diners with a glimpse of the restaurant‚Äôs numerous awards‚Äîan affirmation of its culinary prowess. Reviewers noted mixed experiences with the ambiance; while some appreciated the lively energy, others found it over-cluttered and noisy, detracting from the dining experience. 

Photos reveal a warm and inviting space, with tables adorned with traditional touches, but note the limited room for movement (as seen in the snapshots).

### Menu & Culinary Experience

At the heart of Spice Goa's offerings lies its **Goan Fish Thali**, which garnered rave reviews from visitors. One enthusiastic patron proclaimed it the best they encountered during their six-day visit. This thali comes loaded with a sumptuous arrangement including **prawns curry**, **boneless fish fry**, and delightful sides, culminating with an unexpected treat‚Äî**barfi**. 

In addition to the thali, the restaurant also serves a variety of North Indian dishes, contributing to its broad appeal. Many patrons highlighted the **king fish masala fry**, although opinions on its flavor tweaked towards sourness. Other testaments praised dishes like **chicken lollipops**, while some found the **Goan veg platter** underwhelming for the price. The food is generally well-presented, showcasing the vibrant colors and textures typical of Goan fare, with several drinks and **shakes** available to complement the meal.

### Customer Experience & Service

Customer service at Spice Goa yielded varying experiences. While some diners commended the staff for their friendliness, others reported frustrations, citing slow service and a lack of attentiveness, such as missing essentials like **tissues** and **finger bowls**. Reservations, although encouraged through platforms like **Easy Diner**, may lead to disappointment based on some guests' experiences with booking mishaps. 

Positive notes were logged about the cleanliness of facilities, which speaks to the management's commitment to hygiene, especially important in bustling dining environments.

### Popularity & Reviews

Spice Goa appears to hold a strong foothold in the culinary landscape of Goa, with a steady influx of visitors keen to sample its fare. Beyond customer ratings, it has achieved recognition through numerous awards displayed within the premises. However, it‚Äôs clear that opinions are divided; while many patrons express satisfaction and recommend the restaurant, others have decried it as overhyped and suggested exploring alternative dining options in Goa.

### Utilizing Visual Content

The restaurant's photos encapsulate much of the essence of Spice Goa‚Äîinviting plates of varied dishes, the allure of the fish thali, and glimpses into the restaurant‚Äôs busy atmosphere. One particularly striking image showcases the picturesque layout of a perfectly assembled thali, colors popping and begging to be tasted; another suggests the energetic environment, with diners thoroughly engaged in the experience.

### Conclusion

Spice Goa offers a flavorful adventure into Goan cuisine, making it well-worth a visit if you‚Äôre in the area. While the dining experience may be tinged with minor grievances regarding crowding and service, the standout dishes and spirited ambiance promise to create lasting memories. Prepare for a delicious journey that captures the heart of Goan flavors‚Äîyour taste buds will thank you!
